-- Nigeria Sets Up Committee to Increase Local Processing of Cocoa, NTA Says
-- Vincent Nwanma
-- 2010-07-25T07:42:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/nigeria-sets-up-committee-to-increase-local-processing-of-cocoa-nta-says.html

          
          
             Nigeria set up a committee to come
up with ways of increasing the amount of cocoa thatâ€™s processed
locally, the Nigerian Television Authority reported, citing
Vice-President Mohammed Namandi Sambo.  
 The committee will review the challenges facing Nigerian
cocoa processors and suggest solutions to President  Goodluck Jonathan  within six weeks, the state-owned broadcaster said.  
 Nigeria is the fourth-largest producer of the chocolate-
ingredient, after the  Ivory Coast , Ghana and Indonesia.  
